source.name: US Forest Service Ranger District Boundaries
source.description: A map service displaying the boundary that encompasses a Ranger District. This SDE Geodatabase is intended for read-only use. The purpose of the data is to provide display, identification, and analysis tools for determining current boundary information for Forest Service managers, GIS Specialists, and others. Symbolized with fill and outline Labeling turns on at larger scales Best available source with a target scale of 1:24000 for Continental U.S., Puerto Rico, and Hawaii and 1:63360 for Alaska.
